### Baskonia outlasts Tenerife in Spanish Cup return

Baskonia made it to the Spanish Cup semifinals by topping La Laguna Tenerife 91-81 at Roig Arena on Friday. Baskonia did not trail in this game and relied on [Trent Forrest](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/euroleague/players/trent-forrest/013367/) and [Markus Howard](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/euroleague/players/markus-howard/011948/) to make the difference down the stretch. Forrest led the winners with 21 points. [Rodions Kurucs](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/euroleague/players/rodions-kurucs/005713/) and [Timothe Luwawu-Cabarrot](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/euroleague/players/timothe-luwawu-cabarrot/012080/) each added 14, [Mamadi Diakite](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/euroleague/players/mamadi-diakite/014027/) had 13 while Howard had all of his 10 points in the second half. 

Diakite stepped up early and Trent Forrest soon gave Baskonia a 10-4 lead. Eugene Omoruyi stepped up from Baskonia and Luwawu-Cabarrot hit a 10-meter, buzzer-beating, stop-and-pop three-pointer for a 25-18 lead after 10 minutes. Forrest and Luwawu-Cabarrot kept pacing Baskonia before [Matteo Spagnolo](https://www.euroleaguebasketball.net/en/euroleague/players/matteo-spagnolo/008173/)'s dunk made it a 14-point game, 40-26. Tenerife bounced back but a second buzzer-beater, this time by Kurucs from beyond the arc, restored a 45-33 Baskonia lead at halftime. 

Howard found his first points to boost Baskonia's margin to 49-33 soon after the break. Tenerife went on a 0-11 run which Kurucs stopped with a three-pointer. Tim Abromaitis brought his team as close as 54-53 before Spagnolo, Forrest and Luwawu-Cabarrot gave Baskonia fresh air, 64-60, at the end of the third quarter. Howard and Diakite took over with consecutive three-point plays to boost Baskonia's lead to 77-71 with over 3 minutes remaining. Kurucs buried a critical three-pointer and Howard added 5 points in crunch time to make sure Baskonia kept a safe lead in the final 2 minutes. 

